WEBVTT

00:17.041 --> 00:20.666
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

00:23.041 --> 00:26.750
(CREATURE SCREECHES)

00:50.750 --> 00:52.750
(EPIC MUSIC PLAYING)

01:11.375 --> 01:16.666
MALE NARRATOR: <i>The known universe,</i>
<i>with its heroes and marvels,</i>

01:17.166 --> 01:20.000
<i>but what of the darkness?</i>

01:20.875 --> 01:24.875
<i>In our modern world,</i>
<i>this is where monsters dwell,</i>

01:24.958 --> 01:28.833
<i>alongside those who hunt</i>
<i>and slaughter them with pride.</i>

01:30.041 --> 01:33.333
<i>None more prolific</i>
<i>than the Bloodstone family,</i>

01:33.416 --> 01:39.083
<i>whose patriarch has long controlled</i>
<i>the powerful supernatural relic,</i>

01:39.166 --> 01:43.250
<i>the Bloodstone, a weapon unlike any other.</i>

01:43.333 --> 01:47.750
<i>But now, this weapon</i>
<i>is in want of a new master,</i>

01:47.833 --> 01:51.833
<i>for Ulysses Bloodstone has died.</i>

01:53.583 --> 01:57.000
<i>Tonight is his funeral.</i>

01:59.000 --> 02:02.166
<i>Hunters have gathered</i>
<i>from around the globe,</i>

02:03.666 --> 02:05.666
<i>strangers until this night,</i>

02:06.458 --> 02:12.375
<i>for a ceremonial hunt which will decide</i>
<i>who next will wield the Bloodstone.</i>

02:14.208 --> 02:20.500
<i>And woe to the monster</i>
<i>who finds itself among them.</i>

02:45.541 --> 02:49.458
(ENTHRALLING MUSIC PLAYING)

03:11.208 --> 03:14.416
(OLDIES POP MUSIC
PLAYING ON RECORD)

03:40.000 --> 03:41.250
Elsa's here.

03:54.250 --> 03:55.875
JOSHUA: It's a beauty, innit?

03:57.666 --> 03:59.958
Fifty-seven confirmed kills myself.

04:00.083 --> 04:01.791
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

04:03.166 --> 04:05.250
Next year's my 30th season.

04:05.500 --> 04:07.875
I can almost smell
the blood on your hands.

04:07.958 --> 04:10.000
Thank you.

04:10.250 --> 04:12.875
I like your whole look here
with the makeup.

04:13.000 --> 04:14.291
It's a killer trademark.

04:14.375 --> 04:17.000
Yeah. It's to honor my ancestors.

04:18.250 --> 04:21.041
Yeah. Not much for honoring ancestors
and feelings and all that.

04:21.125 --> 04:23.250
I just know it looks brilliant on you.

04:23.333 --> 04:28.375
I mean, I understand the importance
of anonymity in our line of work,

04:28.458 --> 04:31.250
but it gets lonely.

04:32.583 --> 04:34.125
Just want to say I'm proud

04:34.791 --> 04:37.333
to be honoring old Ulysses
with you here tonight.

04:37.416 --> 04:39.750
Ulysses. Of course.
Hard to believe he's gone.

04:39.833 --> 04:41.625
Aye, the mad bastard.

04:42.958 --> 04:45.416
Quite a place
he built for himself here, eh?

04:46.500 --> 04:50.208
So, any of these hacked beasties
your handiwork?

04:52.208 --> 04:53.333
JACK: No.

04:54.125 --> 04:58.666
No, but... But him.
Him, I fought a few times.

04:59.625 --> 05:01.250
He's never looked so alive.

05:01.333 --> 05:02.708
(CHUCKLES)

05:13.041 --> 05:18.500
Elsa, after 20 years,
I hope you didn't feel obligated to come.

05:18.833 --> 05:23.166
God knows the others won't like it.
How long can we expect you to stay?

05:23.333 --> 05:25.166
Give me what's mine, I'll leave now.

05:25.833 --> 05:28.666
What aspect of Bloodstone
are we after exactly?

05:28.750 --> 05:31.875
The strength it lends, the protection?

05:32.666 --> 05:33.750
Longevity...

05:33.875 --> 05:35.916
Verussa, what I do with it
after I've earned it

05:36.000 --> 05:37.458
will be none of your business.

05:37.541 --> 05:39.583
To be honest, that might be the best part.

05:39.833 --> 05:40.916
(CHUCKLES)

05:42.291 --> 05:46.583
I wonder if you're up to it.
All these years without training...

05:46.666 --> 05:48.333
Without his training.

05:49.958 --> 05:51.291
Let's find out together.

05:51.916 --> 05:53.125
Hmm...

05:53.458 --> 05:55.708
You were so promising growing up.

05:57.041 --> 06:01.041
We all believed
you would surpass your father.

06:02.000 --> 06:05.958
Instead, you seem satisfied
to emulate your mother.

06:07.041 --> 06:08.916
I did what I could with you.

06:09.750 --> 06:11.166
Shame I didn't turn out.

06:11.250 --> 06:13.000
Don't be too easy on yourself.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.583
You were
the greatest disappointment of his life.

06:24.583 --> 06:29.333
Over 200 kills, collectively.

06:31.083 --> 06:33.000
Twenty-six for you.

06:34.041 --> 06:36.291
Thirty-seven kills.

06:36.583 --> 06:38.083
Forty-three.

06:38.583 --> 06:42.125
An impressive 57.

06:42.583 --> 06:47.291
And over 100 deaths, give or take.

06:47.375 --> 06:48.541
Over 100?

06:48.708 --> 06:49.833
Yeah.

06:50.166 --> 06:53.500
So many death dealers in one room.

06:55.750 --> 06:57.208
Oh, my dear heart!

06:57.333 --> 06:58.625
(SCRAPING)

07:04.375 --> 07:08.666
Thank you for gathering in ritual,

07:09.458 --> 07:16.125
for shedding your masks tonight
in honor of Ulysses Bloodstone.

07:17.791 --> 07:18.958
He was a leader,

07:20.958 --> 07:22.291
a friend,

07:22.875 --> 07:26.583
a lover without equal.

07:29.791 --> 07:32.583
Knowing his spirit would not be
with us tonight

07:32.666 --> 07:35.541
to state his wishes
for the ceremonial hunt,

07:35.625 --> 07:40.375
he orchestrated his presence
in other ways.

07:40.625 --> 07:43.000
(LAUGHS)

07:43.083 --> 07:45.375
Incorrigible, really.

07:59.583 --> 08:01.875
(MACHINERY CRANKING)

08:17.166 --> 08:21.750
I do hope my attendance delights you.

08:23.791 --> 08:27.333
Thank you, Verussa, for seeing it through

08:27.416 --> 08:30.666
and for shaping our cause like no other.

08:30.833 --> 08:32.000
Oh!

08:32.208 --> 08:37.583
With my passing,
it is now time to choose a new leader

08:37.666 --> 08:41.000
in the crusade against monsters.

08:41.083 --> 08:45.583
This honor can only be bestowed upon

08:45.666 --> 08:50.291
the strongest
and most committed to our mission.

08:50.750 --> 08:55.333
Very soon, a monster
unlike anything you've faced

08:55.416 --> 08:59.375
will be released
into these sacred grounds.

09:00.125 --> 09:05.875
The hunter who slays this beast
will become our new leader,

09:06.250 --> 09:10.291
taking possession of my Bloodstone.

09:10.375 --> 09:12.791
Good luck.

09:12.916 --> 09:16.958
I'll be rotting for you.

09:17.583 --> 09:19.416
-(CHUCKLES)
-(VERUSSA LAUGHS)

09:22.333 --> 09:25.625
Oh, forgive me. Graveyard humor.

09:37.500 --> 09:40.250
There is only one Bloodstone,

09:41.916 --> 09:45.541
and it can have only one keeper.

09:46.458 --> 09:52.083
It was to be his daughter's,
but through decades of absence,

09:52.833 --> 09:56.541
Elsa has long forsaken that birthright.

09:58.791 --> 10:00.875
The only weapons permitted tonight

10:00.958 --> 10:04.375
have been placed throughout the garden
for you to find.

10:06.583 --> 10:08.958
Per my husband's wishes,

10:10.708 --> 10:15.666
the stone will be affixed
to the monster's hide.

10:17.166 --> 10:18.958
This will weaken it.

10:19.833 --> 10:24.291
It will also make it angry.

10:29.000 --> 10:30.000
Hang on.

10:30.083 --> 10:34.958
The stone's finally up for grabs
and we all earned the right to hunt,

10:35.041 --> 10:37.458
but she gets to crash this thing
like it's a backyard wedding?

10:37.541 --> 10:42.000
He brings up a good point.
Where's the lovely lady's medallion?

10:42.291 --> 10:43.875
Have you checked up your own arse?

10:43.958 --> 10:46.541
Elsa is welcome to join.

10:46.708 --> 10:51.041
And like the rest of you, she's fair game.

10:52.625 --> 10:55.958
No special treatment.

11:00.041 --> 11:01.916
Those who do not survive

11:02.916 --> 11:07.000
will be honored appropriately.

11:07.166 --> 11:09.750
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

11:10.333 --> 11:17.041
<i>For tonight,</i>
<i>it is every hunter for themselves.</i>

11:38.666 --> 11:40.500
Ya lucky bastard.

11:41.250 --> 11:43.125
VERUSSA: You shall go first.

11:46.333 --> 11:48.333
The others will follow.

11:48.500 --> 11:50.458
MAN 1: Right there, come on.

11:51.041 --> 11:52.875
-(MAN 1 YELLS)
-(MONSTER GROWLING)

11:53.708 --> 11:55.250
(MAN 1 GROANING)

11:55.458 --> 11:56.916
(MONSTER ROARS)

11:57.083 --> 11:58.458
MAN 1: Put her out, put her out!

11:58.541 --> 11:59.791
MAN 2: Let's move.
MAN 1: Close the gates.

11:59.875 --> 12:02.041
(MONSTER ROARS)

12:04.583 --> 12:06.875
I'd say the stone was in place.

12:08.916 --> 12:10.291
Off you go.

12:10.666 --> 12:12.416
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

12:23.208 --> 12:25.083
And now, we pledge.

12:26.166 --> 12:29.625
We spill all blood for the hunt.

12:30.083 --> 12:35.208
ALL: For stone and creed,
for those who forged our blade.

12:35.291 --> 12:38.750
To rid this land of its abominations.

12:40.208 --> 12:45.375
ALL: There is no peace without blood,
and so it shall be.

12:45.916 --> 12:47.875
And so it shall be.

12:48.541 --> 12:50.416
And so it shall be.

12:51.125 --> 12:52.791
And so it shall be.

12:53.458 --> 12:55.666
And so it shall be.

12:56.208 --> 12:58.208
And so it shall be.

12:58.958 --> 13:00.833
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

14:27.625 --> 14:31.125
(MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE)

15:17.250 --> 15:18.250
(MUSIC STOPS)

15:43.750 --> 15:47.625
I suggest we just pass each other by.

15:47.750 --> 15:48.916
What?

15:50.583 --> 15:53.458
I suggest we just pass each other by.

15:53.583 --> 15:54.833
(JOSHUA GRUNTS)

15:55.666 --> 15:57.041
(ELSA GRUNTS)

15:59.083 --> 16:03.000
The stone is mine!

16:03.458 --> 16:04.625
(GRUNTS)

16:04.708 --> 16:05.958
(PANTING)

16:06.166 --> 16:07.333
(GRUNTS)

16:13.708 --> 16:15.583
(BOTH GRUNTING)

16:16.583 --> 16:17.666
(ELSA CHUCKLES)

16:19.166 --> 16:22.000
Death is coming for you, lassie!

16:22.958 --> 16:24.500
(MONSTER SNARLS)

17:09.791 --> 17:11.083
(EXHALES)

17:17.625 --> 17:19.041
(RUSTLING)

17:51.041 --> 17:53.291
(BOTH GRUNTING)

18:02.291 --> 18:04.041
-(GRUNTS)
-(YELLING)

18:04.416 --> 18:06.875
(GROANING)

18:17.625 --> 18:19.250
-(YELLING)
-(GRUNTS)

18:27.875 --> 18:29.041
(ELSA YELLS)

18:29.750 --> 18:31.083
(GROANS)

18:36.458 --> 18:37.791
(GRUNTS)

18:51.041 --> 18:52.500
(CHOKING)

19:18.500 --> 19:19.875
(CHUCKLES)

19:25.625 --> 19:27.166
(MONSTER ROARS)

19:33.541 --> 19:35.208
(MONSTER SNARLS)

19:56.708 --> 19:58.250
(GASPS AND LAUGHS)

20:00.666 --> 20:03.916
Hey. Hey. What's up?

20:04.916 --> 20:07.291
Well, of course I was gonna come find you.

20:07.375 --> 20:09.083
Of course. Are you okay?

20:09.541 --> 20:10.791
(MONSTER SNARLS)

20:11.000 --> 20:13.500
You keep saying
that you're gonna be careful each time,

20:13.583 --> 20:15.250
and here we go again.

20:15.333 --> 20:18.750
You can't keep counting on me to save you.
This is the last time.

20:18.916 --> 20:21.000
(MONSTER GRUNTS)

20:21.083 --> 20:23.708
I know. Does it hurt?

20:23.791 --> 20:26.375
-(MONSTER GRUNTS)
-It's weakening you, right?

20:27.125 --> 20:29.208
Yeah, they said that
the stone would do that.

20:30.833 --> 20:33.041
Don't worry, I have a plan.

20:33.583 --> 20:37.500
Look, so apparently,
these little things explode.

20:38.333 --> 20:40.375
So, we're gonna
explode our way out of here.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.625
All you have to do is don't die.

20:42.708 --> 20:44.833
Don't... Just keep alive.

20:45.083 --> 20:48.208
I'm gonna figure out where to put this,
and I'll come get you.

20:48.291 --> 20:49.958
-I'll find you. I don't know.
-(MONSTER GROWLS)

20:52.250 --> 20:53.875
-(SNARLS)
-(GRUNTS)

21:06.083 --> 21:08.416
No, no, no, don't close the...

21:08.500 --> 21:09.541
Door.

21:11.666 --> 21:13.000
(SIGHS)

21:15.291 --> 21:16.833
Well, that's great.

21:17.000 --> 21:18.666
(GRUNTING)

21:28.291 --> 21:29.625
How's your night going?

21:29.708 --> 21:31.916
Well, it's going.

21:33.833 --> 21:35.083
Difficult.

21:36.625 --> 21:37.833
You hurt?

21:38.208 --> 21:39.666
-Can I help you?
-No.

21:41.333 --> 21:42.458
Okay.

21:46.125 --> 21:47.416
But it's bleeding a lot.

21:49.625 --> 21:52.125
It has to be tight and even.

21:52.375 --> 21:53.875
Wow, thank you for that.

21:55.250 --> 21:57.250
Me, I have to get out of here.

21:57.333 --> 21:58.541
Oh, and you think I don't?

21:59.708 --> 22:02.500
I came to get the stone
'cause I want to be rid of my dad,

22:02.583 --> 22:05.833
my stepmother, all of this for good.
Now, I'm stuck in here with some...

22:05.916 --> 22:06.916
Oh, that's tight.

22:07.000 --> 22:08.041
Can I take a look?

22:09.500 --> 22:12.375
It has to be done right,
because if not, it's not gonna work.

22:26.916 --> 22:30.375
You didn't want to fight before either,
did you, running into me?

22:31.583 --> 22:34.000
Then that maniac with the axe,
hell, you didn't fight.

22:34.708 --> 22:37.666
I'm having a hard time believing
you hunted and killed monsters.

22:37.750 --> 22:39.958
Well, I'm not that type of hunter.

22:40.750 --> 22:42.583
At least
not like those <i>esbirros</i> out there.

22:42.791 --> 22:44.125
Yeah, well, neither am I.

22:46.416 --> 22:49.083
No? It's not in your DNA then?

22:53.875 --> 22:56.333
If you're not a hunter,
why do you want the stone?

23:01.666 --> 23:02.666
I don't.

23:05.416 --> 23:07.250
That's not the reason why I'm here.

23:08.250 --> 23:10.250
You know, maybe we can help each other.

23:11.291 --> 23:14.625
If you help me
get the monster out of here alive,

23:15.833 --> 23:17.083
I can get you the stone.

23:18.583 --> 23:21.625
Right, yeah. 'Cause you'll just have
a quick chat with him,

23:21.708 --> 23:24.375
sort it out 'cause you're, what,
the monster's friend?

23:26.875 --> 23:28.000
(SCOFFS)

23:32.166 --> 23:33.208
(GROANS)

23:40.958 --> 23:42.875
So, you don't wanna be
like your father, then?

23:42.958 --> 23:43.958
Careful.

23:44.791 --> 23:48.166
I understand. It must be complicated
to grow up with this family.

23:48.250 --> 23:50.333
You have no idea about my family, none.

23:50.458 --> 23:51.583
I don't.

23:53.833 --> 23:55.791
I can tell you my family was different.

23:57.333 --> 23:59.500
But all families have something in common.

24:01.333 --> 24:02.416
They follow us.

24:04.500 --> 24:09.666
For good, for bad.
They stay, like they become an atmosphere.

24:12.625 --> 24:16.500
And sometimes, we think that
by doing something very specific,

24:16.583 --> 24:19.750
we can change everything,
and not be like them.

24:23.500 --> 24:25.083
(MONSTER ROARS)

24:27.291 --> 24:29.625
Or sometimes,
they're just a pain in the ass

24:29.708 --> 24:31.791
that we have to save all the time.

24:36.250 --> 24:37.333
I don't know.

24:38.791 --> 24:39.833
It's complicated.

24:43.750 --> 24:45.000
We could die here.

24:48.208 --> 24:49.958
You and I, with your family.

24:51.208 --> 24:54.291
It's an option.
It's not my choice, but it's an option.

25:10.208 --> 25:11.250
(GRUNTS)

25:18.833 --> 25:19.916
JACK: What are you doing?

25:20.000 --> 25:21.125
ELSA: When I was a kid,

25:21.208 --> 25:24.041
my dad used to tell me stories
about my crazy Aunt Frances.

25:31.583 --> 25:33.416
He said that if I misbehaved,

25:34.500 --> 25:36.291
she would unlock her tomb

25:36.666 --> 25:39.625
and come out and pull me back in there
with her for company.

25:40.375 --> 25:44.125
She was positive that she'd come back
from the dead at some point, and she knew

25:45.250 --> 25:47.250
that when she did, she'd need...

25:49.208 --> 25:50.333
That's not bad.

25:52.916 --> 25:53.916
Ooh!

25:56.541 --> 25:57.791
...an exit strategy.

26:08.375 --> 26:11.666
Well done, Elsa.
My name is Jack, by the way.

26:11.750 --> 26:14.375
Okay, Jack, you blow the wall,
I'll get him to you.

26:14.458 --> 26:18.000
Okay, I trust you. I'm trusting you, okay?

26:18.125 --> 26:19.625
Just get me the stone and we're good.

26:20.458 --> 26:22.208
Then you're on your own.

26:25.750 --> 26:30.458
Okay. Closest perimeter wall is that way,
straight shot, then two lefts and a right.

26:30.875 --> 26:32.875
There's a massive crack
about halfway down.

26:32.958 --> 26:35.000
As soon as you get there,
turn on the explosive.

26:35.083 --> 26:36.958
Throw it at the wall, then get clear.

26:37.041 --> 26:38.083
Okay.

26:38.166 --> 26:40.833
And, Jack, cross me
and I'll kill you both.

26:41.833 --> 26:42.875
Okay.

26:42.958 --> 26:46.000
Hey, when you run into him, just...

26:47.458 --> 26:51.083
Just treat him like an old friend.
Call him by his name.

26:51.166 --> 26:52.416
Which is?

26:52.500 --> 26:54.916
Ted. He's called Ted.

26:56.583 --> 26:57.791
Ted?

26:58.375 --> 26:59.416
Yeah.

27:00.583 --> 27:03.208
How do you turn this on?
Because I've been trying...

27:03.375 --> 27:04.750
(BEEPING)

27:05.041 --> 27:06.208
No.

27:14.375 --> 27:15.625
(TED SNARLS)

27:31.375 --> 27:32.458
Hey!

27:39.875 --> 27:41.958
(JOSHUA SCREAMING)

27:45.083 --> 27:46.208
(SHUDDERS)

27:48.791 --> 27:50.208
(ROARS)

27:55.416 --> 27:56.666
Ted?

27:56.750 --> 27:57.833
(TED GRUNTS SOFTLY)

27:58.541 --> 28:01.375
You have a lovely name.

28:02.541 --> 28:06.958
And your friend is waiting for you.

28:10.333 --> 28:11.500
(PANTING)

28:16.916 --> 28:18.666
(DEVICE BEEPING)

28:29.666 --> 28:31.250
(DEVICE BEEPING RAPIDLY)

28:50.041 --> 28:51.208
No!

28:53.583 --> 28:54.666
(PANTING)

29:00.000 --> 29:01.041
(GRUNTS)

29:03.583 --> 29:04.750
Wait!

29:08.000 --> 29:09.083
(GRUNTS)

29:11.416 --> 29:12.916
(SNARLS)

29:20.291 --> 29:21.750
(TED ROARS)

29:24.041 --> 29:25.208
(CHUCKLES)

29:30.250 --> 29:31.375
(GRUNTS)

29:35.208 --> 29:36.333
(GROANS SOFTLY)

29:51.791 --> 29:54.916
Well, now, look at this.

29:56.291 --> 29:58.416
The Bloodstone did this to you?

29:59.291 --> 30:02.083
He grabbed it and it threw him back.

30:05.666 --> 30:06.833
My word.

30:10.208 --> 30:11.500
A monster.

30:13.583 --> 30:16.375
Masquerading as one of our own.

30:17.291 --> 30:20.250
Desecrating a sacred night.

30:22.625 --> 30:24.083
(GROANS)

30:25.291 --> 30:27.666
And you? What was the thinking here?

30:27.958 --> 30:30.083
You freed a monster with a monster?

30:30.208 --> 30:31.583
I didn't know that bit.

30:32.666 --> 30:33.708
Well,

30:35.916 --> 30:40.583
I can't wait to find out
what breed of evil you are.

30:42.416 --> 30:44.291
None of you should have the stone.

30:44.708 --> 30:46.375
The hunt decides!

30:46.500 --> 30:47.708
-(CRACKLES)
-(GROANS)

30:53.666 --> 30:54.833
House rules.

31:17.625 --> 31:20.750
No. No, no, no, no...

31:21.166 --> 31:23.166
(SIGHS) No.

31:33.583 --> 31:34.750
Elsa?

31:39.458 --> 31:42.375
Elsa. Are you okay?

31:44.833 --> 31:47.416
Until you rip my throat out,
I suppose I'm fine.

31:48.833 --> 31:52.500
I... am sorry.

31:53.375 --> 31:56.500
I couldn't tell you, you know.
It wasn't safe.

31:56.583 --> 31:59.000
What, did you think it might
cloud my judgment a bit?

31:59.458 --> 32:02.500
Yeah, I know, I'm an idiot. I know.

32:03.833 --> 32:05.291
But I'm also a human.

32:06.875 --> 32:11.125
Perhaps not in the category
that you would call a human a human.

32:13.833 --> 32:17.208
You see, I've got systems
to manage the hurt I could cause...

32:17.291 --> 32:20.000
I don't care about your systems.

32:20.083 --> 32:22.083
Just stay away from me until you can't.

32:22.166 --> 32:25.500
But they work. You'd be surprised.
They actually work.

32:26.166 --> 32:27.416
'Cause I'm not like that.

32:28.500 --> 32:30.833
I'm like this, you know. I'm...

32:31.541 --> 32:34.625
I would never hurt you
or hurt any one of them.

32:35.166 --> 32:41.666
And any hunting that I do is done
by a part of me that is not me.

32:42.666 --> 32:44.958
And that's not the part
you're with right now.

32:48.833 --> 32:50.541
So you got nothing to worry about.

32:50.958 --> 32:55.500
Because I lock myself in once a month,
every full moon.

32:55.791 --> 32:57.041
That's it.

32:57.125 --> 33:00.000
And the next full moon is in five days.

33:00.083 --> 33:02.791
We have plenty of time
to figure something out.

33:02.875 --> 33:04.583
You don't get it, mate.

33:06.833 --> 33:08.958
Why do you think they put me
in here with you?

33:10.166 --> 33:11.250
Five days?

33:11.916 --> 33:15.000
The Bloodstone's capable
of transforming you in five seconds.

33:17.791 --> 33:19.916
Thanks in advance for making it quick.

33:37.750 --> 33:38.875
No, no.

33:45.541 --> 33:47.416
I shouldn't have asked for your help.

33:48.166 --> 33:49.958
Yeah, well, I shouldn't have needed yours.

33:50.041 --> 33:52.791
-This is gonna be really bad.
-Bloody stupid. (SNIFFLES)

33:56.541 --> 33:58.958
(FOOTSTEPS THUMPING IN DISTANCE)

34:01.000 --> 34:02.916
Okay, okay.

34:03.666 --> 34:06.458
So, if this is gonna happen,
I need you to look at me. Okay?

34:06.750 --> 34:08.541
Do not break eye contact, no matter what.

34:08.625 --> 34:10.166
What are you talking about?

34:10.708 --> 34:12.791
What are you doing? What the...

34:14.291 --> 34:15.291
Get...

34:16.333 --> 34:17.916
And this is what?

34:18.208 --> 34:20.166
I need to remember you. (SNIFFING)

34:21.291 --> 34:22.583
Well, does it work?

34:26.625 --> 34:27.625
Once...

34:35.250 --> 34:36.583
I'm asking you, please.

34:37.958 --> 34:39.208
Please don't do this.

34:40.291 --> 34:41.416
Not this way.

34:46.208 --> 34:47.625
Just kill me as I am.

34:49.750 --> 34:51.916
Otherwise there will be no mercy,
I promise.

35:12.458 --> 35:13.625
Mercy?

35:18.583 --> 35:20.166
This may surprise you,

35:20.791 --> 35:24.958
our whole mission is built
on mercy for you,

35:25.875 --> 35:27.750
and those like you,

35:29.291 --> 35:33.375
as well as
all the innocent lives you take.

35:35.916 --> 35:39.208
You'll wanna see this, darling.

35:39.666 --> 35:45.291
Your father died convinced
you'd never come home. I lived in hope.

35:45.416 --> 35:47.833
I wonder how he'd feel
about you hunting me.

35:47.916 --> 35:50.208
Better than he'd feel about your betrayal.

35:51.125 --> 35:55.666
But once this is over,
you'll notice my hands are clean.

35:55.750 --> 35:59.375
His? Mmm, not so much.

36:04.291 --> 36:08.583
It's time for you to show yourself.

36:12.791 --> 36:15.250
(CHANTING IN LATIN)

36:31.875 --> 36:33.125
I'm sorry, Elsa.

